cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DS

This paper primarily focuses on privacy and security issues related to wireless communication networks, specifically cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of existing cellular infrastructure and the optimization of user utility, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper presents and evaluates a deanonymization algorithm, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
